pageContext.claim: “Well look at what happened, we just did 3.2 [percent quarterly GDP growth] and frankly if we would have had the Obama interest rates -- you know, where they kept them very low, which is not necessarily good, but if we would have had those low interest rates we could have been much higher than that. But 3.2 is a number that they haven't hit in 14 years.”
pageContext.analysis: False. The U.S. had GDP growth of 3.3 percent in the first quarter of 2015.
